The global ball valves market is witnessing significant growth due to the increasing demand for energy across various end-use industries such as oil and gas, water and wastewater, chemicals, and others. The market is segmented based on type, material, and size. The type segment includes floating ball valves, trunnion mounted ball valves, rising stem ball valves, and three-way ball valves. Among these, the rising stem ball valves segment is expected to witness substantial growth due to their high efficiency and control capabilities.

In terms of materials, the market is further segmented into stainless steel, cast iron, alloy-based, cryogenic, and others. Stainless steel ball valves are widely used across industries due to their corrosion resistance and durability. The increasing focus on industrial automation and the need for efficient flow control mechanisms are driving the demand for ball valves made from stainless steel.

