The increasing demand for energy worldwide is a major driver of the ball valves market growth. The oil and gas industry, in particular, has a significant impact on the market as ball valves are widely used in exploration, production, refining, and distribution processes. The water and wastewater industry also plays a crucial role in driving market growth, as ball valves are essential for regulating the flow of water and ensuring efficient operations of treatment plants and distribution systems. The chemicals industry is another major end-user of ball valves, where these valves are used for controlling the flow of various chemicals in manufacturing processes.

